<h1> Messenger bot </h1>

<p> Welcome to the Bot Messenger app! Bot is very friendly and wants to know you better! Start the conversation by typing a greeting message üñê</p>

<h2>Rules for conversation: </h2>
<ul>
  <li> Greeting: "hi", "hey", "hello"</li>
  <li> Accepting: "yup", "yes", "yeah", "sure", "yep", "i do"</li>
  <li> Denying: "no", "nah", "nope", "not now", "maybe later"</li>
  <li> Gratitude: "thanks", "thx", "thank you", "thank you very much", "thanks a lot", "thanks!", "thank you!" </li>
</ul>

<h2> Maintaining the conversation </h2>
<p> Bot is still very early on his learning phase, so you should try to correctly answer the questions and choosing answers from given cards, although you can manually type messages.</p>

<button> <a href="https://github.com/JusticeBringer/Node.js-Messenger-Bot/blob/master/readme.md#demo-conversation" target="_blank"> See demo conversation </a> </button>

<!-- Load Facebook SDK for JavaScript -->
<div id="fb-root"></div>
<script>
  window.fbAsyncInit = function() {
    FB.init({
      xfbml            : true,
      version          : 'v8.0'
    });
  };

  (function(d, s, id) {
  var js, fjs = d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0];
  if (d.getElementById(id)) return;
  js = d.createElement(s); js.id = id;
  js.src = 'https://connect.facebook.net/en_US/sdk/xfbml.customerchat.js';
  fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js, fjs);
}(document, 'script', 'facebook-jssdk'));</script>

<!-- Your Chat Plugin code -->
<div class="fb-customerchat"
  attribution=setup_tool
  page_id="101149528396924"
    theme_color="#0084ff"
    logged_in_greeting="Hi! Would you like to answer a few questions about yourself?"
    logged_out_greeting="Hi! Would you like to answer a few questions about yourself?">
</div>

</body>
</html>
